The upgrade is complete. Here's a summary of what was produced:

**`tech_zugferd-spec.md`** — 1,855 lines (~95% TPL-SVC v1.0.0 compliance)

The spec documents the ZUGFeRD E-Invoicing Service as a **fully stateless transformer** (per ADR-TECH-003), which required adapting the template in three places: §3 uses request/response value objects instead of persistent aggregates, §7 explicitly states "None" for events, and §8 has no database tables. All four decisions are documented in §14.2.

Key content added:
- **§3**: 3 operation models, 6 enumerations (including all 6 ZUGFeRD profiles with business descriptions), 6 shared types (`InvoiceData`, `PartyInfo`, `MonetaryAmount`, `InvoiceLineItem`, `ValidationError`, plus one more)
- **§4**: 13 business rules (BR-ZF-001–013), 6 detailed definitions, full validation table, reference data dependencies (bundled classpath resources)
- **§5**: 4 use cases with full detail; cross-domain invoice generation workflow (RPT → ZUGFeRD → DMS)
- **§6**: 4 REST endpoints (`/embed`, `/validate`, `/extract`, `/info`) with realistic JSON request/response examples including a complete EN16931 invoice embed
- **§12**: 3 extension events, 2 rule slots, 3 aggregate hooks with hook contracts
- **§13**: SAP FI/SD migration mapping; `/api/t1/zugferd/v1` deprecation (6-month sunset per ADR-TECH-004)

**`tech-zugferd-changelog.md`** and **`tech-zugferd-open-questions.md`** created with 9 open questions (Q-ZF-001 through Q-ZF-009) covering port assignment, file size, ISO validation strategy, OAuth2 scoping, capacity planning, feature dependencies, extension API design, and ZUGFeRD 1.0 backward compatibility.
